# docloom-studio/Dockerfile builds from this (repository root) context. Keep
# it to source only: the image runs its own npm ci / pip install and never
# needs these on disk already, some of them (.venv, node_modules) are
# hundreds of MB, and shipping .git defeats layer caching on every commit.
.git/
**/_git_backup/
**/__pycache__/
**/*.py[cod]
**/.venv/
**/venv/
**/.pytest_cache/
**/*.egg-info/
**/.mypy_cache/
**/.ruff_cache/
**/node_modules/
**/web/dist/
**/.vite/
docloom/examples/output/
docloom/examples/out_ui/
examples/output/
